Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.61,0:14:25.07,Main,Act3,0,0,0,,He has disappeared! {S-H-I-T}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.07,0:14:26.07,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.07,0:14:29.83,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,There's no way he could escape \N 3 Freeze's range so easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.62,0:14:37.35,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'll only say this once more; \N don't even think about following me.{The Japanese phrasing is different. First time it was "otte konaide", so "Don't follow me (please)", and here it's "otte kuru nante kangaenaide yo", so "Please don't think of such a thing as following me". -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.71,0:14:41.67,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I hate repeating myself \N when saying things once should suffice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.67,0:14:45.19,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Repeating oneself is pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.19,0:14:47.30,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I say this for your own well being.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.30,0:14:49.43,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Never take pointless actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.32,0:14:52.68,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Knock him down, Act 3!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.10,0:15:01.02,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,M-My attack on the tree came back at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.02,0:15:03.36,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I took something of yours...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.53,0:15:10.74,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yet based on the damage you were dealt, \N you were clearly holding back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.12,0:15:13.45,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You're a good person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.04,0:15:19.75,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,It's clear to me now...\NGiorno Giovanna...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.75,0:15:22.71,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,He's... a Stand user! {ASTUTE OBSERVATION CAPTAIN OBVIOUS} {ikr? also y no split? split @ He's... -JMFW}
Comment: 0,0:15:32.45,0:15:32.49,Main,,0,0,0,,D
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.92,0:15:40.79,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Hello? {WHO ARE YOU? WHO IN FACE ARE YOU?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.79,0:15:42.84,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,Mr. Jotaro, it's Koichi! {Guanglai Kangyi, age 15}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.84,0:15:46.22,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Oh, Koichi. \N Did you arrive in Italy yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.22,0:15:47.38,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,I found him! {should this be in the Narrator style, or Thoughts style? This is inconsistent throughout the phone conversation -JMFW}{Going ahead and making them all narrator for consistency with DiU (or at least a DiU phone scene I picked at random that I didn't bother comparing to other scenes). - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.38,0:15:50.68,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,The guy you asked me to find! \N Shiobana Haruno!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.68,0:15:52.22,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,That was fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.22,0:15:54.68,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Where do I even begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.68,0:15:56.89,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I ran into him almost \N immediately at the airport...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.89,0:16:00.39,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,O-Oh, right. \N Long story short...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.39,0:16:02.35,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,...he's a Stand user!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.69,0:16:05.40,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,He goes by the name \N Giorno Giovanna in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.40,0:16:07.28,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,Didn't you say it yourself, Mr. Jotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.28,0:16:10.11,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,Stand users are drawn \N to other Stand users. {Actually Hazamada is the first person in the series to say it, BUT HEY}{Hazamada was indeed the first person to say it in the series, but he only told it to Jotaro and Josuke. Jotaro was the first person to tell it to Koichi! -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.11,0:16:12.91,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,We met by complete coincidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.91,0:16:15.62,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,He's a student who acts like a gangster.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.62,0:16:18.41,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,He stole my luggage and all my money!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.41,0:16:23.88,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,And his Stand's ability seems to have something to do with \N returning his opponent's attacks right back at them. {THAT'S WHAT YOU THINK}{Added a "seems to have" instead of "has" here, since the JP line contains "osoraku", making it clear that this is just Koichi's assumption. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.88,0:16:25.42,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,I'm sorry that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.42,0:16:28.55,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,I'll get you a hotel reservation \N and wire you some money.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.55,0:16:29.97,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.97,0:16:32.72,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,Also, unlike in the photo, \N his hair is blond now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.72,0:16:36.60,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,I asked a few people who knew about him, \N and they said he didn't dye it. {split at the comma and the keyframe? -JMFW}{Lines are too short for this amount of text, I think it reads better as-is -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.60,0:16:39.39,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,It suddenly changed color \N not too long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.39,0:16:41.98,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,It has something to do with \N his late father's genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.98,0:16:43.57,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,Who exactly is his father?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.65,0:16:47.48,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,Do you have some kind of \N connection to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.99,0:16:53.90,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,I'm the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.90,0:16:56.03,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,...who killed his father. {he pissed me off, so sorry not sorry}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.74,0:16:59.08,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,His name was Dio Brando.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:01.20,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Dio?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.20,0:17:03.79,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,You mean the same Dio \N involved with the bow and arrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.79,0:17:08.34,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,This year, I discovered it was possible \N that Dio may have had a child. {sired, really... so much for being a dad}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.34,0:17:17.18,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,That's why I wanted to verify if Giorno Giovanna \N was really Dio's son, as well as if he inherited any of his traits.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:20.68,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,But doesn't Dio's body \N belong to the Joestar bloodline? {thanks Koichi}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.68,0:17:28.77,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,His hair turning blond may be proof that \N Dio's blood awakened inside him, bringing out his Stand ability.{Yeah, it sounds a bit odd to say that "Dio's blood awakened in him", but... that's what he's saying. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.77,0:17:31.23,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Something may have triggered it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.23,0:17:35.07,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,...such as a powerful Stand user \N living within the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.07,0:17:37.62,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,A powerful Stand user?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.62,0:17:39.70,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Don't approach him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.70,0:17:41.08,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,It's too dangerous to proceed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.71,0:17:42.54,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.25,0:17:47.00,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,One last thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.38,0:17:49.22,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Is he our enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.22,0:17:51.71,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Or is he our ally?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.55,0:17:54.39,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.39,0:17:56.05,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,You actually met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:57.81,Narrator,Jotaro,0,0,0,,What's your impression of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.52,0:18:02.90,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.90,0:18:03.97,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.97,0:18:06.64,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,He had this...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.64,0:18:08.40,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,...serene feeling about him. {Split and rewrite as: "He had this..."/"...serene feeling about him." -JMFW}{Gyro, you can implement Jules' change exactly as he wrote it if you think it works -J}{Done -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.45,0:18:26.75,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Is this yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.75,0:18:27.71,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.09,0:18:30.21,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.21,0:18:31.84,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Guess it's mine, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.13,0:18:40.09,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Suppose you happened upon \N a bag containing one billion unmarked lire...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.09,0:18:41.14,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Would you turn it in?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.10,0:18:44.72,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Never. I'd keep it to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.90,0:18:47.48,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,My, my, aren't you honest?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.48,0:18:51.82,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,But what if I were a plainclothes police officer \N and saw you take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.49,0:18:58.45,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'd give you half \N so you'd look the other way, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.04,0:19:03.66,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Wow, good answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.66,0:19:06.33,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,I can tell that's exactly what you would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.33,0:19:08.29,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,You're not joking or bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.29,0:19:11.92,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,I can really tell! \N You're being honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.92,0:19:16.51,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Funnily enough, I can tell when \N someone is being honest with me or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.51,0:19:18.85,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,I'm rarely ever mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.85,0:19:21.89,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,You know how your skin \N glistens a bit when you sweat?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.89,0:19:23.80,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,That's how I do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.80,0:19:28.27,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,If I can taste the sweat, \N it gives me an even better impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.02,0:19:32.36,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Who exactly are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.40,0:19:39.66,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,"Leaky-eye" Luca was found on the ground near the airport \N with the imprint of his spade smashed into his skull.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.66,0:19:42.91,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,It was a life-threatening injury. \N He'll never regain consciousness again. {I think "life-threatening" is too mild for an injury that put someone into a permanent coma. -Gyro}{The JP literally just says "He'll never regain consciousness again. His condition is severe." Honestly... I feel like we can probably just leave it at "He'll never regain consciousness again."? -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.91,0:19:45.71,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,I'm looking for the individual responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.71,0:19:51.50,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Giorno Giovanna, nobody knows \N what "Leaky-eye" Luca was doing at the airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.50,0:19:58.30,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,However, the airport security guards \N kindly informed me that you were present at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.30,0:20:02.18,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,That's why I came here \N to ask you some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.60,0:20:04.55,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Are you an actual police officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.55,0:20:05.94,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.94,0:20:10.40,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Luca's no ordinary thug. \N He's a gangster. {Consistency with later episodes? "gangster" instead of "gang member"? -JMFW}{Axel, keep track of this -J} {I was gonna suggest "gang member" too since he says it and since Luca was shortlived in the series, but I'll keep track. -Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.40,0:20:12.52,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,He could have been taken out \N for any number of reasons. {"for someone taking him out"? -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.52,0:20:15.53,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,He's the kind of person \N people hold grudges against.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.53,0:20:16.48,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.48,0:20:20.32,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,...none of that is any concern of the boss. {Starfish, check this line for accuracy -J}{Literally "What his boss is thinking about is not that." I think this edit works. Only thing is that he specifically states "HIS" boss, rather than just "THE" boss. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.32,0:20:25.16,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,The boss feels slighted from \N one of his own being incapacitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.16,0:20:29.79,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,That's why he ordered me to \N find and settle matters with the perpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.79,0:20:32.13,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,So answer me this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.13,0:20:36.13,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Did you run into "Leaky-eye" Luca at the airport?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.59,0:20:38.59,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No. I don't know who that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.81,0:20:52.19,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,You aren't sweating...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.19,0:20:54.02,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Fine. I believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.10,0:20:57.03,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,That's all I wanted to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.03,0:21:00.03,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Sorry for bothering you, Giorno Giovanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.16,0:21:14.42,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.42,0:21:15.96,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Even though my hand was clenched...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.96,0:21:17.75,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,That was Luca's right eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.01,0:21:21.34,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,He was unconscious, \N so I brought it with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.47,0:21:28.64,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,This taste... is the taste of a liar, \N Giorno Giovanna! {but does he taste like cherries}{It's a well-known fact that liars taste like milk that's slightly past its due date. -Starfish} {I thought he tastes like expired onions.- Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.72,0:21:32.85,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Well, well, well, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.85,0:21:39.69,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,{\pos(1230,1045)}I said I was done asking questions, \N but the situation has changed, Giorno Giovanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.57,0:21:42.82,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,You lied to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.82,0:21:49.49,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,{\pos(1160,1045)}I do believe I'm obligated to find out \N just why you were lying to me, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.20,0:21:53.88,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,What are you staring at?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.88,0:21:55.29,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Jealous?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.29,0:21:57.42,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,{\pos(860,1045)}Would you like to hit him, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.96,0:22:01.84,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,{\pos(1000,1045)}My name is Bruno Buccellati. {Blono Bucciarati*}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.84,0:22:03.22,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Now answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.22,0:22:06.88,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,This interrogation has already \N turned into a torture session.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.26,0:22:14.22,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Well? \N It's a pretty unnerving ability, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.22,0:22:15.48,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Th-These are...!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.48,0:22:17.94,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,They're Luca's fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.94,0:22:19.57,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.57,0:22:23.45,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,{\pos(890,1045)}The boss already disposed \N of "Leaky-eye" Luca.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.45,0:22:26.28,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,{\pos(790,1045)}He saw no reason to keep him alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.28,0:22:29.91,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,I took his fingers to assist in torturing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.16,0:22:29.50,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,It happened again! What did he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.33,0:22:34.08,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Could he have an ability \N like that Japanese tourist?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.08,0:22:38.84,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,{\pos(1066.286,1045)}In addition to knowing whether or not \N someone is lying, I can also do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.84,0:22:43.30,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,I can put whatever I like in your mouth. {This is such low hanging fruit that I'm only leaving this comment here as proof that I resisted -J} {I can't: "OR YOUR BUTT" -JMFW} {( ͡° ͜ʖ ͡°)}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.30,0:22:44.55,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,For example...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.55,0:22:48.38,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,{\pos(1050,1045)}If I liked, I could put that \N entire fire extinguisher inside your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.97,0:22:52.81,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Though you would \N die in an instant if I did. {nah, i think he could take it all} {( ͡° ͜ʖ ͡°)}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.27,0:22:58.31,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Now talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.31,0:23:01.28,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,You saw the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.28,0:23:03.07,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Were you told to stay quiet?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.07,0:23:06.94,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Why don't you start by telling me \N who had it out for Luca?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.82,0:23:12.33,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,There's no doubt in my mind... \N We have similar abilities!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.33,0:23:16.21,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,Unless you hurry up and tell me, \N the torture will continue...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.21,0:23:18.29,Main,Buccellati,0,0,0,,...Giorno Giovanna!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.42,0:23:25.05,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,This guy is dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.93,0:23:28.35,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,I have no choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.81,0:23:35.02,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,I have to use Gold Experience \N to dodge his attacks!
